Every year in videography we have to make a documentary to make people understand the importance of a certain topic. 
This year i decided to choose a topic that i thought was something that really needed to be said. 
Stereotypes

Teenagers are always walking down the hallway and looking at other people saying oh look it's a punk or a goth or a prep. And honestly i have to say i have done it to but ever since i have thought about this topic i have really tried to stop myself and just think about people as themselves. I took a survey and i found that when it comes down to it teens classify themselves mostly into a clique called the individualists. 
Being placed into a stereotypical clique has caused a women personal harm. 
Not that long ago a women entered a local "hang out" place to buy some things that she needed becuase she had just moved in.
Since she had just moved to the town she didn't know that the place she had just entered had a bad reputation. 
When she entered a group of men grabed her and raped her over and over again. 
They threw her against a pool table and raped her.
The men around the pool table acted like cheerleaders. 
A witness said why should i care? he was obliviously one of the cheerleaders. 
The only reason that this young women was raped was because of the way she looked. becuase of the way she was dressed. Suposidly she was dressed as if she was a whore as if she was wanting to be raped they said it was something she desirved for looking the way she did. But does the way a person look make it right. NO. Her rapping was going to go down in history as the worst raping they have ever seen. 
But unfortunatly the women died 2 yrs later fue to a drunk driver.
A local citizen said, "i like spectator sports, football, basketball, hockey, but that, that is jsut sick, to cheer as aonther women is being rapped."
TO many things that shouldn't happen are happening simply becuase of the way we dress and because people place people into stereotypes. 
I can't change everything, all i can do is to strongly suggest that you stop and understand the issue at hand as i have already realized the problem and i know im going to try and stop it.

                                                              *thank you* ~shannon carson~
